16 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code Title 23, Chapter 81, Subchapter 1, is
17 amended to add an additional section to read as follows:
18 23-81-138. Application for life insurance — Discrimination based on
19 organ donor status prohibited — Definitions.
20 (a) As used in this section:
21 (1)(A) "Life insurer" means an entity that enters into a
22 contract that incorporates mortality risk, including an annuity contract.
23 (B) "Life insurer" includes without limitation an insurer
24 issuing life insurance contracts that grant additional benefits in the event
25 of an insured's disability; and
26 (2) "Living organ donor" means an individual who has donated all
27 or part of an organ and is not deceased.
28 (b) A life insurer authorized to transact the business of insurance in
29 this state shall not cancel, limit, or deny life insurance coverage or
30 establish any differential in premium rates based on an individual's status
31 as a living organ donor.
32 (c) A life insurer shall not consider an individual's decision to be a
33 living organ donor for any insurance purpose.
